1
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:47,120
The Earth

2
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:50,640
holds within it the most captivating
symmetry and connection.

3
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,480
Divided by the equator and its meridians

4
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:55,120
into the Northern
and Southern Hemispheres,

5
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:58,720
the two halves follow
entirely opposite seasonal rhythms.

6
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:01,280
With their vastly different
geography, texture,

7
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,400
and climate,

8
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,920
they have given rise to civilizations
of strikingly distinct character.

9
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,640
The vast continents
of the Northern Hemisphere

10
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:10,360
nurture a depth of cultural heritage
and character.

11
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:13,120
The expansive oceans
cradling the Southern Hemisphere

12
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:16,200
give rise to clarity and raw vitality.

13
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,880
The natural wonders it nurtures

14
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:20,320
are nothing short of rare treasures.

15
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,840
This time,

16
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:24,400
the Earth Group
will unlock the Southern Hemisphere,

17
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:27,040
following the thread of
the 40th parallels north and south,

18
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,680
exploring through differences,

19
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,600
and understanding through connections.

20
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:33,040
(Christopher Luxon, Prime Minister of New Zealand)
Wow The World S2.

21
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:33,344
(Lu Nan, Member of
the New Zealand Parliament)

22
00:01:33,344 --> 00:01:35,680
Welcome to New Zealand.

23
